episodes.title: The Trump Presidency - A Religious Cult? Reza Aslan explains
episodes.description:
Reza Aslan argues that Donald Trump has turned much of American evangelical Christianity into a religious cult. This cult consists of:
- a deeply insular social group bound together by extreme devotion to a charismatic leader who is elevated to prophetic and near divine status.
- the leader has a self-ascribed role as the one true source of information, and is believed by his followers to possess special knowledge and truth.
- the cult leader fosters a siege mentality among followers and posits himself as the antidote. 
- cult members believe they are fighting in a battle between good and evil.

Reza also warns that the Trump presidency disintegrating spells great danger as cults will double-down when prophecy fails and their leader becomes a martyr.

episodes.title: How a Sociopath Grew a Conscience: The Ground-breaking Case of Shawn McCraney
episodes.description:
Preview 00:00
Introduction  01:43

PART I - MAKING OF A SOCIOPATH  02:47

Empathy and being different 02:53
Manipulation and Control 09:55
Fear and Abandonment  13:21
Anger and Violence 14:19

PART II - TRANSFORMATION & CHANGE 50:20

Seeking out mental health care 50:25
The Roadside Experience 55:13
Taking the HARE Psychopathy Test 01:12:58
Developing a conscience 01:14:29
Leaving Mormonism and Re-Understanding Sin and Harm 01:34:01
Why should we believe you? 01:40:13

PART III - CONTINUANCE & THE FUTURE 01:41:53

Identity Warfare 01:41:58
Living without God 01:44:26
A bio-psycho-social or a spiritual explanation? 01:58:11
Life's Journey 02:02:05

Conclusion 02:02:58

Pastor Shawn McCraney was diagnosed with sociopathy (anti-social personality disorder) as a young man and exhibited all the predatory traits associated with this condition. After having a family, seeking out mental health support, having a religious epiphany at a roadside and then leaving Mormonism, Shawn found a way to develop empathy and grow a conscience. He is living proof that sociopathy need not be permanent.

This interview is part of a series titled 'Sociopathy: An Option Undiscovered' (https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLLw52gGEoMGlD9qfC_iBgcJPoYsqTkLcq) where  cases such as Shawn's are presented to the public.

I reached out to Shawn after Shawn revealed some of his history on the podcast Mormon Stories, and I began the task of documenting his life story. We are currently producing a book titled "Sociopathy: An Option Undiscovered: The Ground-Breaking Case of Shawn McCraney" which will compile our transcribed interviews, contributions from Shawn's family and friends, along with expert commentary from academic researchers, professionals and clinicians. Our hope is to contribute to the clinical study and societal understanding of anti-social personality disorder. If you would like to contribute to the book , please reach out at mattb.virtualresearcher@gmail.com.

episodes.title: Fact Check: David Ownby on Falun Gong
episodes.description:
What Ownby gets right:
- that Falun Gong has, over time, solidified and developed a much stronger organizational structure
- the parallel (to some extent) with Scientology
- their refusal to answer questions that they disagree with
- the tunnel vision within the group

What Ownby gets wrong:
- that Falun Gong does not take money from its practitioners
- that Falun Gong does not encourage any form of separation of Falun Gong practitioners from their family and friends.

"Only a cynical man would call what these people have lives. Crime, despair - this was not how man was supposed to live.

The League of Shadows has been a check against human corruption for thousands of years. We sacked Rome, loaded trade ships with plague rats, burned London to the ground. Every time a civilization reaches the pinnacle of its decadence, we return to restore the balance. When a forest grows too wild, a purging fire is inevitable and natural. 

Tomorrow the world will watch in horror as its greatest city destroys itself. The movement back to harmony will be unstoppable this time. Over the ages, our weapons have grown more sophisticated. With Gotham, we tried a new one: economics. Create enough hunger and everyone becomes a criminal. 

We are back to finish the job, and this time no misguided idealists will get in the way, who lack the courage to do all that is necessary. If someone stands in the way of true justice, you simply walk behind them and stab them in the heart"

episodes.description:
The powerful will always exist in one form or another because humankind is weak. We are weak. The powerful control everything, except our will to choose. 

Heroes don't accept the way the world is. The powerful may be eternal, but we can make their existence painful. We can bring their gears to a grinding halt even just for a moment. Power endures. We can't take down the powerful but for one bright shining moment we can show them that they don't own us. You need to decide for yourselves whether that's worth fighting for.
